race.comment: MORAVIA (6) dropped considerably in grade and led all the way for an effortless win over 1400m at Eagle Farm last start. Dropping back to 1200m and shouldering a big weight from a wide alley are negatives, but on the class side of things he has a bit on this field. SCRIPTED (14) blew the start then did a good job to finish midfield in the Magic Millions mares' race over 1300m at the Gold Coast five weeks ago. Form prior to that was hard to knock. This looks a perfect race while a bit on the fresh side. ABENDER (1) was ridden closer to the pace and got the job done most recently in a BM68 over this course and distance. Loves the 1200m here and is a chance again despite the wide draw. AMUSEANTES (11) missed the kick then rattled home late for fourth over this trip at Eagle Farm last start. Blinkers on may see a bit more early energy. Worth considering. The lightly raced ZOUFANI (16) wasn't far away first-up and will improve off that run.
